               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-169-person1660">
                  THOMAS 
                  PAYNE
               <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1660" type="surname" value="PAYNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1660" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1660" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18270913-169-viclabel961" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-169-victim1659 t18270913-169-viclabel961"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18270913-169-crimeloc962">Charles-street, Globe-fields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-169-crimeloc962" type="placeName" value="Charles-street, Globe-fields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-169-crimeloc962" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-169-off959 t18270913-169-crimeloc962"></join> - I missed my watch when I was going to bed on the 22d of July; it was safe at<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182709130099"></xptr>twenty minutes before seven o'clock that evening; the prisoner lodged with me, and came home that evening at twenty minutes before seven, and went out again; he came home at eleven o'clock, and I then gave charge of him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Will you swear that he had not left the house at half-past six o'clock? A. I will take my oath, that he came in between twenty minutes before seven and seven.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-169-person1661">
                  LEVY 
                  SOLOMON
               <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1661" type="surname" value="SOLOMON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1661" type="given" value="LEVY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1661" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Rosemary-lane, about a mile from Globe-fields. As I stood at my door on the Sunday in question, the prisoner came and offered me a watch, and said he wanted money - I offered him 15s., and he agreed to take 18s., which I gave him; this was between nine and ten o'clock in the evening.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Had you ever seen him before? A. No. I do not know whether this is a usual time for selling watches, but I keep my Sabbath on a Saturday - I gave the watch to my son-in-law.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-169-person1662">
                  JOHN 
                  JACOBS
               <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1662" type="surname" value="JACOBS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1662" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1662" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Mr. Solomon gave me this watch, and I put it into my pocket. I afterwards gave it to the officer.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. How came you to give it to the officer? A. I was minding another shop for my father-in-law, and I shewed it to a fellow-shopman; we had some dispute about the value of it, and I said "Go to the pawnbroker's next door, and ask what they would lend upon it;" they said 1l.; the pawnbroker then gave information of it, and the officer came and took it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-169-person1663">
                  ROBERT 
                  DAVIS
               <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1663" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1663" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1663" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I produce this watch which I got from Jacobs on the Monday. The prisoner was apprehended on the Sunday.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-169-person1664">
                  JOHN 
                  BRADMAN
               <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1664" type="surname" value="BRADMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1664" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-person1664" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I took charge of the prisoner on the Sunday night; I was going by at half-past ten o'clock, and Mr. Payne told me, if I saw the prisoner to take him; while I was there, he came home, and I took him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>MR. PHILLIPS to MR. PAYNE. Q. Was there not a young woman in your house? A. There was a young woman out of place, who slept with my daughter; but from the time she came in, till she went to bed, I kept sight of her; the seals of my watch were in my hat in the room where the prisoner slept; they were covered with this handkerchief; if he chose he might have taken them, but they were only brass.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270913-169-verdict963" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-169-verdict963" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 26.</p>
               <p>
